# The setgid permission on a file is very similar to setuid; it allows a user to run an executable binary file in a manner that provides them additional (temporary) group access.

ls -l /usr/bin/wall
-rwxr-sr-x 1 root tty 35048 May 30  2023 /usr/bin/wall

To add setgid permission numerically add 2000;
chmod 2770 [dir name]

To remove setgid permission numerically:
chmod 0770 [dir name]


To set setgid permission symbolically add 2000;
chmod g+s [dir name]


To remove setgid permission symbollically:
chmod g-s [dir name]

